<table><thead><tr><th scope="col">Notes</th>
<th scope="col">Explanation</th>
</tr></thead><tbody><tr><td id="A">A</td>
<td>When rates changed prior to 29 December 1988, the first payment at the new rate was made on the family allowance payday after the date shown.</td>
</tr><tr><td id="B">B</td>
<td>Since January 1990, CDA rates are indexed every January.</td>
</tr><tr><td id="C">C</td>
<td>Includes a $2.15 a week ($4.30pf) ad hoc increase announced in the 1991-92 Budget.</td>
</tr><tr><td id="D">D</td>
<td>CDA and DNCB were replaced by CA from 1 July 1999.</td>
</tr></tbody></table><div class="reference">
